text: Hello Guys, Which endpoints can provide me the web analytics history data? ( Like page seen, event revenue, number of views, etc custom fields )
Hey, <@UGXQK1B7Y>. Could you share the error you received?

Hey, <@UBQSVT1HA>. You can get high level analytics data (similar to what’s available in the Traffic Analytics and Website Analytics tools) via the Analytics API (<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/methods/analytics/analytics-overview>).

If you’re referring to getting the web analytics history of a specific contact, you can use the Contacts API to pull the values and history of any contact property (e.g. _Last page seen_, `hs_analytics_last_url`), but there is currently no way to get a history of page views, sessions, etc. for contacts. See this similar Community post: <https://community.HubSpot.com/t5/APIs-Integrations/Downloading-page-view-data-for-all-contacts/m-p/277483>.
